"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61765","Home Office","false","2014-06-19","<p> </p><p>Home Office Ministers have meetings with and make visits to a wide variety of international partners, as well as organisations and individuals in the public and private sectors, as part of the process of policy development and delivery.</p><p><br>Details of these meetings and visits are passed to the Cabinet Office on a quarterly basis and are subsequently published on the Gov.uk website:<br>http://data.gov.uk/dataset/ministerial-data-home-office</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-06-19T15:45:37.8434071Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61765/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61765/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61765/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-12","Official Visits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what visits each of the Ministers in her Department have made since January 2013; and what the purpose of each such visit was.","false","Biography information for Sheila Gilmore","Edinburgh East","Sheila Gilmore","200488"
