"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61784","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-19","<p> </p><p>According to departmental records DFID answered all parliamentary questions that required a substantive answer before the 2014 prorogation.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-06-19T13:15:43.0888095Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61784/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61784/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61784/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-12","Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many parliamentary questions tabled to her Department in the last parliamentary Session did not receive a substantive answer by the time of the 2014 prorogation; and when each such question was first tabled.","false","Biography information for Alison Seabeck","Plymouth, Moor View","Alison Seabeck","200447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61785","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-19","<p>Israeli movement and access restrictions do tremendous damage to the Palestinian economy; the World Bank has estimated that easing restrictions on Area C alone could increase Palestinian GDP by 35%. In Gaza, Israeli restrictions on movements of goods and people do tremendous damage to the economy and living standards of ordinary people. 80% of the households in Gaza are below the poverty line, and 57% are food insecure. The UN predicts that by 2020 Gaza may no longer be a ‘liveable' place.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-06-19T13:15:05.4280476Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61785/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61785/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61785/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-12","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what research her Department has undertaken into the humanitarian effects of the occupation of the West Bank and the blockade of Gaza.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Corbyn","Islington North","Jeremy Corbyn","200411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61786","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-18","<p>The humanitarian crisis in Syria has reached catastrophic proportions. The UN estimates that 9.3 million people are in dire need of humanitarian aid within Syria. At least 6.5 million people in Syria have been forced to flee their homes to other areas of the country and there are now over 2.8 million refugees in the region.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-06-18T16:19:31.8443556Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61786/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61786/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61786/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-12","Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent assessment she has made of the humanitarian situation in Syria.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","200347"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61787","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-19","<p>Tackling the humanitarian crisis in Yemen, where we are one of the largest humanitarian donors, is a priority for DFID. As such, DFID ministers have played a leading role in galvanising international efforts and encouraging others to do more. This has involved regular discussions with senior global leaders both in the specifically convened Friends of Yemen, but also during regular meetings with partners to discuss humanitarian issues.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-06-19T15:52:21.379227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61787/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61787/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61787/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-12","Yemen","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many meetings she has had with world leaders to discuss the humanitarian situation in Yemen since 1 January 2013.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","200357"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61788","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-19","<p>DFID is one of the largest humanitarian donors to Yemen. We are committed to tackling the humanitarian crisis in the country including through the £70m of human assistance we offered in 2013. Last financial year we offered £32m of assistance, we have already allocated £33m for this year and the balance of the commitment will be allocated as soon as possible.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-06-19T15:49:07.7454906Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61788/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61788/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61788/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-12","Yemen","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much of the £70 million which her Department offered to Yemen in 2013 for emergency food assistance, shelter, clean water and help for people recovering from conflict was provided to that country.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","200355"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61789","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-18","<p> </p><p>As I announced on Saturday, the UK is providing an initial £3 million of emergency humanitarian assistance to help civilians fleeing the ISIL advance in Northern Iraq. Following an assessment of needs on the ground by DFID humanitarian experts who deployed to Erbil last Thursday, this includes:</p><p> </p><p>(i) – Activation of the UK's Rapid Response Facility (RRF), which provides emergency support via pre-approved organisations in the event of a humanitarian crisis overseas. This initial package of UK support comprises clean water and sanitation, essential medicine, women-friendly hygiene kits and basic household items, which will be provided from £2 million of RRF funding to NGOs in the region.</p><p> </p><p>(ii) - Protection for vulnerable girls and women through the deployment of dedicated UN safety and welfare teams in key internally displaced person and refugee camp sites and areas, secured through £1 million of funding to the UNHCR.</p><p>The UK will continue to monitor the situation closely and we are considering urgently what other assistance we could provide.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-06-18T15:40:37.35368Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61789/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61789/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61789/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-12","Iraq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she plans to increase the UK's humanitarian contribution to Iraq.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","200571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61790","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-19","<p> </p><p>Details of all overseas visits undertaken by DFID Ministers are published under the transparency section of the DFID website and can be found at:</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dfid-secretary-of-state-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings-with-external-organisations</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dfid-minister-of-state-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings-with-external-organisations</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dfid-parliamentary-under-secretary-of-state-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings-with-external-organisations</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-06-19T13:16:22.4334381Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61790/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61790/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61790/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-12","Official Visits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what visits each of the Ministers in her Department have made since January 2013; and what the purpose of each such visit was.","false","Biography information for Sheila Gilmore","Edinburgh East","Sheila Gilmore","200489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61791","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-19","<p> </p><p>DFID has already committed £33m in assistance for this financial year and we are in the process of assessing where we should allocate further funds and at what scale.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-06-19T15:53:52.504784Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61791/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61791/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61791/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-12","Yemen","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what the budgeted spend is for humanitarian aid for Yemen for the next two years.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","200427"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61793","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-06-19","<p /> <p /> <p>The Department is not able to provide this information without incurring disproportionate cost because this would require extensive searches of all current and former Ministers' diaries over this period and further research to confirm the purpose of each visit.</p><p> </p><p>I can confirm that Ministers from this Department go on regular visits which are relevant to their portfolios, including to courts and tribunals, prisons, probation services and a wide range of organisations connected to the Department's work.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-06-19T15:35:09.1839622Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61793/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61793/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61793/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-12","Official Visits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what visits each of the Ministers in his Department have made since January 2013; and what the purpose of each such visit was.","false","Biography information for Sheila Gilmore","Edinburgh East","Sheila Gilmore","200490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61794","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-06-19","<p /> <p /> <p>The Ministry of Justice received3,087 questions tabled in the Commons during the 2013-14 session. Of these,26 parliamentary questions did not receive a substantive answer by the end of the last session. In these cases the relevant Minister committed to write providing a substantive answer and the written responses. We have now answered 16 of the outstanding questions and are in the process of responding to the remaining 10. The following table sets out the month in which each of the questions was tabled.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>February 2014</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>March 2014</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2014</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May 2014</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Justice Secretary and his Ministerial team take their obligations to Parliament seriously and want to ensure that MPs receive answers of a high standard which set out the relevant context. More complex questions can involve compiling and analysing large volumes of material. We respond to such questions as promptly as we can.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-06-19T15:51:14.160716Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61794/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61794/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61794/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-12","Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many parliamentary questions tabled to his Department in the last parliamentary Session did not receive a substantive answer by the time of the 2014 prorogation; and when each such question was first tabled.","false","Biography information for Alison Seabeck","Plymouth, Moor View","Alison Seabeck","200448"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61795","Home Office","false","2014-06-18","<p>The police provide the Home Office with aggregated figures of the recorded number of racially or religiously aggravated assault with (a) and (b) without injury offences. It is not possible to separately identify the specific aggravating factor. <br><br>In the year ending December 2013, the police recorded 2,473 racially or religiously aggravated assault with injury offences and 3,988 racially or religiously aggravated assault without injury offences.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-06-18T15:54:32.701925Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61795/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61795/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61795/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-12","Racially Aggravated Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many racially aggravated attacks were recorded in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","200511"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61796","Leader of the House","false","2014-06-16","<p>In February 2013, I visited the Scottish Parliament to examine Parliamentary procedures and practices.</p><p>In May 2013, the Deputy Leader of the House and I undertook an overseas visit to the European Institutions in Brussels. This visit provided an opportunity to consider and promote the role of national parliaments, including the House of Commons, in the processes of European legislation.</p><p>In December 2013, the Deputy Leader of the House visited Northern Ireland to engage with various Northern Irish charities and campaign groups on the Transparency of Lobbying, Non-Party Campaigning and Trade Union Administration Bill.</p><p>In February 2014, I and the Deputy Leader of the House visited the Welsh Assembly in Cardiff to examine Parliamentary procedures and the work of the Petitions Committee.</p>","South Cambridgeshire","Mr Andrew Lansley",,"2014-06-16T15:24:30.5984225Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61796/answer","Biography information for Lord Lansley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61796/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61796/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2014-06-12","Official Visits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, what visits each of the Ministers in his Office have made since January 2013; and what the purpose of each such visit was.","false","Biography information for Sheila Gilmore","Edinburgh East","Sheila Gilmore","200491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61797","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-06-19","<p> </p><p>Details of Ministers' visits overseas are published quarterly and can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=northern-ireland-office" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=northern-ireland-office</a>.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-06-19T12:53:25.5658317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61797/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61797/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61797/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-06-12","Official Visits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what visits each of the Ministers in her Department have made since January 2013; and what the purpose of each such visit was.","false","Biography information for Sheila Gilmore","Edinburgh East","Sheila Gilmore","200492"
