"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61799","Prime Minister","false","2014-06-17","<p>I plan to hold wide-ranging discussions with Premier Li. We have a foreign policy that is based on our values, and we consistently raise them with the Chinese government, including during high level dialogues.</p><p> </p><p>I am very supportive of the business and human rights agenda, and action against climate change is a priority for the government.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","200462 ; 200469","2014-06-17T15:54:03.523385Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61799/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61799/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61799/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2014-06-12","China","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if he will discuss climate change with his Chinese counterpart during his visit to the UK.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","200468"
