"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61326","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-06-17","<p>We welcome the US presence on Diego Garcia, and we have said we want to see it continue. The current agreement does not conclude until December 2016, and we have not yet held substantive discussions with the US about this subject. I expect my officials to begin doing so later this year.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-06-17T08:55:58.6148801Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61326/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61326/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61326/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-06-11","British Indian Ocean Territory","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his US counterpart on the extension of the lease for Diego Garcia Airbase.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace","200200"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61327","Department for Education","false","2014-06-18","<p>The Government is giving more schools greater flexibility to adapt the shape of the school year in the interests of their pupils' education.</p><p>Whilst this will extend an existing flexibility to a greater number of schools, our advice will continue to include a clear expectation of schools working with each other and the local authority to coordinate dates to avoid unnecessary disruption to parents and their employers.</p><p>The Department has consulted with representatives of the tourist industry. Where schools choose to change their holiday dates, following discussion locally with parents and local businesses, there may well be a positive impact on seaside economies. In areas of high-seasonal employment, for example, small variations to term-dates agreed locally may help parents to holiday outside of peak periods.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-06-18T16:26:11.9349467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61327/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61327/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61327/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-11","Academic Year","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what economic assessment he has made on the effect on tourism jobs in seaside areas and seaside economies of deregulating school holidays.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace","200272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61328","Department for Education","false","2014-06-16","<p>The Control of Asbestos Regulations 2012 set out the standards and duties to manage asbestos in non-domestic premises including schools. This includes the need to assess and manage the risks through the formulation of a site-specific asbestos management plan.</p><p> </p><p>On 24 January I announced the 2014-15 maintenance allocations, which are released as a non-ringfenced capital grant. The priorities for its use are decided locally and this can include supporting schools with asbestos issues.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-06-16T14:30:33.4403506Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61328/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61328/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61328/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-11","Schools: Asbestos","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assistance his Department makes available to schools to survey for and remove asbestos.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace","200229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61329","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-06-16","<p>Taking Part child survey results for activity by individual art forms are not regularly published broken down by BAME. This requires further analysis of the underlying survey data and we will publish this analysis in the libraries of both Houses.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-06-16T14:51:48.877589Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61329/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61329/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61329/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-06-11","Arts: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what proportion of primary pupils of each ethnic background and in total have engaged with (a) theatre activities, (b) music activities, (c) dance and (d) other arts in each year since 2009-10.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","200181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61330","Scotland Office","false","2014-06-17","<p> </p><p>According to Glasgow City Council figures (November 2013), there are approximately 18,000 businesses in Glasgow. The Scotland Office holds no information on the ownership nationality of companies located in neither Glasgow North West nor Glasgow.</p><p>However, across the UK as a whole, over 99% of private sector businesses will be small and medium sized enterprises (SMEs) and ownership for these is therefore highly likely to be based locally.</p><p>In 2013, registered private sector enterprises with ultimate ownership outside Scotland accounted for 3.1% of firms. These are disproportionately larger firms and so account for over 35% of employment. This suggests that 96.9% of businesses in Scotland have Scottish ownership, accounting for 64.8% of employment.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-06-17T14:21:11.663886Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61330/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61330/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61330/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-06-11","Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what information he holds on the proportion of companies in (a) Glasgow North West, (b) Glasgow and (c) Scotland are ultimately owned by companies based in (i) Scotland, (ii) other parts of the UK, (iii) other countries in the EU and (iv) outside the EU.","false","Biography information for John Robertson","Glasgow North West","John Robertson","200202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61331","Scotland Office","false","2014-06-17","<p>There are no estimates of the number of companies headquartered in Scotland, of the 343,105 enterprises operating in Scotland as at March 2013. Registered private sector enterprises with ultimate ownership outside Scotland accounted for 3.1% of firms, and 58.1% of turnover. This means that 41.9% of business turnover in Scotland is generated by enterprises with ownership in Scotland. These figures come from the Scottish Government publication Businesses in Scotland 2013.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-06-17T14:17:57.564649Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61331/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61331/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61331/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-06-11","Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, if he will estimate the revenue generated in Scotland by companies that have their headquarters (a) in Scotland and (b) outside of Scotland.","false","Biography information for John Robertson","Glasgow North West","John Robertson","200203"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61332","Department of Health","false","2014-06-18","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) has advised that providing all the information in the format requested would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Information about technology appraisals where NICE has recommended a technology only in circumstances in which a patient has not been treated with a previously recommended technology can be found within each published technology appraisal on NICE's website at:</p><p> </p><p>www.nice.org.uk</p><p> </p><p>Information about where NICE has considered or made recommendations regarding the sequential use of technologies can also be found within each published technology appraisal on the website.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","200234","2014-06-18T15:07:41.9801893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61332/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61332/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61332/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, in which single or multiple technology appraisals for pharmacological treatments for cancer the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) has considered the sequential use of the appraised technology with another available treatment; and whether in each such appraisal this resulted in a recommendation on sequential use in each year since NICE was established.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","200238"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61333","Department of Health","false","2014-06-18","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) has advised that providing all the information in the format requested would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Information about technology appraisals where NICE has recommended a technology only in circumstances in which a patient has not been treated with a previously recommended technology can be found within each published technology appraisal on NICE's website at:</p><p> </p><p>www.nice.org.uk</p><p> </p><p>Information about where NICE has considered or made recommendations regarding the sequential use of technologies can also be found within each published technology appraisal on the website.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","200238","2014-06-18T15:07:41.8830863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61333/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61333/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61333/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what (a) pharmacological treatments and (b) associated indications the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence has recommended only for patients who have not been treated with a previously appraised drug.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","200234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61334","Department of Health","false","2014-06-18","<p>The consideration of end of life criteria was introduced into the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence's (NICE) technology appraisal process in January 2009. NICE has advised that it has recommended the following treatments for prostate, lung, bowel and kidney cancer under its technology appraisal programme where the end of life criteria were applied. No treatments for breast cancer have been recommended under the end of life criteria.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Cancer</p></td><td><p>Appraisal</p></td><td><p>Technolo-gy appraisal</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Prostate</p></td><td><p>abiraterone in combination with prednisone or prednisolone for the treatment of castration-resistant metastatic prostate cancer previously treated with one docetaxel-containing regimen</p></td><td><p>TA259</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p>Lung</p></td><td><p>oral topotecan for small cell lung cancer</p></td><td><p>TA184</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>pemetrexed (maintenance treatment) for non-small cell lung cancer</p></td><td><p>TA190</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bowel</p></td><td><p>sunitinib for gastrointestinal stromal tumours</p></td><td><p>TA179</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p>Kidney</p></td><td><p>sunitinib (first-line) for renal cell carcinoma</p></td><td><p>TA169</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>pazopanib for the first-line treatment of advanced renal cell carcinoma</p></td><td><p>TA215</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em>Source</em>: National Institute for Health and Care Excellence</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-06-18T15:11:00.1141425Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61334/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61334/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61334/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what (a) pharmacological treatments and (b) associated indications the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) has recommended for (i) prostate cancer, (ii) lung cancer, (iii) bowel cancer, (iv) breast cancer and (v) kidney cancer through either single or multiple technology appraisals and under the end of life criteria in each year since NICE was established.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","200233"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61335","Department of Health","false","2014-06-18","<p>This information is not collected by the Department or NHS England.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-06-18T15:04:47.4586795Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61335/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61335/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61335/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many patients have not received homecare medicines and products on time for treatment of (a) cystic fibrosis, (b) HIV and (c) rheumatoid arthritis in the last year.","false","Biography information for Jason McCartney","Colne Valley","Jason McCartney","200204"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61336","Department of Health","false","2014-06-18","<p>It is estimated that between 2009 and 2013 approximately 49,000 forms were returned to registered medical practitioners (RMPs) for further information and clarification.</p><p> </p><p>Form HSA4 already requires information to be provided as to whether the two certifying RMPs saw and/or examined the pregnant woman.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","200274","2014-06-18T15:36:17.6132667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61336/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61336/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61336/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many HSA4 certificates his Department has returned to terminating doctors pending completion in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","200273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61337","Department of Health","false","2014-06-18","<p>It is estimated that between 2009 and 2013 approximately 49,000 forms were returned to registered medical practitioners (RMPs) for further information and clarification.</p><p> </p><p>Form HSA4 already requires information to be provided as to whether the two certifying RMPs saw and/or examined the pregnant woman.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","200273","2014-06-18T15:36:17.4413935Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61337/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61337/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61337/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to amend the HS4A abortion notification form to require registered medical practitioners to indicate whether they have examined the presenting patient and/or discussed with her the grounds for abortion prior to forming their opinion in good faith that the provisions of the Abortion Act 1967 were met.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","200274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61338","Home Office","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p>Claims for asylum are increasing. In 2013 the number of asylum applications <br>within the EU was the highest it has been since 2002. The UK has experienced an increase <br>of 30% between 2010 and 2013 – with an 8% increase between 2012 and 2013 alone.<br><br>We are committed to resolving these quickly, while continuing to improve <br>the quality of our decision making, and we are making changes to our processes <br>and management to make sure we do so.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-06-23T11:26:33.4814238Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61338/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61338/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61338/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-11","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to speed up claims by asylum seekers.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","200219"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61339","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-06-16","<p>President Abbas was clear that new interim technocratic government will uphold a commitment to the principle of non-violence, a negotiated two state solution, and an acceptance of all previous agreements and obligations, including Israel's legitimate right to exist. Reuniting Gaza and the West Bank under a government committed to these principles is a necessary condition for resolving the Israel-Palestinian conflict. We now look to the new government to demonstrate these commitments through its actions as well as its words.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-06-16T12:10:20.5717683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61339/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61339/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61339/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-06-11","Middle East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the approach of the new Palestinian government to the peace process with Israel.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","200310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61340","Department of Health","false","2014-06-18","<p>Information is not available in the format requested.</p><p> </p><p>Information on the number of children aged up to 18 years, registered in primary and secondary care, that were newly diagnosed with type 1 diabetes in 2009-10, 2010-11 and 2011-12 in the former (a) North Staffordshire Primary Care Trust (PCT), (b) South Staffordshire PCT and (c) Stoke-on-Trent PCT, is shown in the following table.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2009-10</p></td><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>2011-12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North Staffordshire PCT</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>25</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South Staffordshire PCT</p></td><td><p>23</p></td><td><p>23</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Stoke on Trent</p><p>PCT</p></td><td><p>15</p></td><td><p>9</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em> </em></p><p><em>Source: </em>The Health and Social Care Information Centre – National Diabetes Audit</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><em>Notes: </em></p><p>1. Participation in the National Diabetes Audit (NDA), which audits diabetes registrations in primary and secondary care, is not mandatory. The NDA does not have 100% coverage or participation and therefore cannot accurately provide the information requested.</p><p>2. The Royal College of Paediatrics and Child Health are the authoritative source for all Paediatric diabetes audit data.</p><p>3. 2012-13 data has not yet been published. The NDA currently only holds data for 2009-10, 2010-11 and 2011-12.</p><p>4. Information is not available by constituency.</p><p>5. The NDA provides data on the number of children aged up to 18 years that were newly diagnosed with type 1 diabetes, which is synonymous to the number of children who began treatment.</p><p>6. To protect patient confidentiality, figures between one and five inclusive have been replaced with *.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-06-18T15:16:03.8308635Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61340/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61340/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61340/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","Diabetes: Staffordshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many children began treatment for Type 1 diabetes in (a) Cannock Chase constituency and (b) Staffordshire in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Aidan Burley","Cannock Chase","Mr Aidan Burley","200241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61341","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-18","<p> </p><p>Information on the number of Apprenticeship starts by Sector Subject Area and geography is published in a supplementary table to a Statistical First Release (SFR):</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships--2</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/308418/apprenticeship-starts-by-region-and-sector-subject-area.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/308418/apprenticeship-starts-by-region-and-sector-subject-area.xls</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-06-18T15:36:47.4493451Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61341/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61341/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61341/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-11","Apprentices: Staffordshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many apprenticeships commenced in each sector in (a) Cannock Chase constituency and (b) Staffordshire in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Aidan Burley","Cannock Chase","Mr Aidan Burley","200236"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61342","Cabinet Office","false","2014-06-16","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-06-16T12:18:08.012652Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61342/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61342/answer","PQ 200237.pdf","PQ 200237.pdf","ONS Letter to Member","ONS Letter to Member","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61342/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-06-11","Employment: Cannock Chase","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of women in Cannock Chase constituency were in work in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Aidan Burley","Cannock Chase","Mr Aidan Burley","200237"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61343","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-17","<p>We are giving employers control of the funding for the training and assessment of the apprenticeships that they design. This will enable them to work directly with education and training providers to secure the most effective training for their apprentices. We will be testing a new funding model via apprenticeship starts in the 2014-15 academic year based on standards developed by our Trailblazer groups of employers. We will develop a comprehensive communication programme for employers (including local authorities) to help them understand the changes.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-06-17T09:50:05.5483094Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61343/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61343/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61343/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-11","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what support his Department is giving to local authorities to implement changes to apprenticeship funding.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","200172"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61344","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-17","<p>Discussions have been held with a wide range of training providers as well with the Association of Training Providers and Association of Employment and Learning Providers (AELP) about our apprenticeship funding reforms. I spoke about this issue at the AELP's National Conference earlier this month.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-06-17T09:53:05.6176Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61344/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61344/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61344/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-11","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent discussions he has had with training providers on changes to apprenticeship funding.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","200173"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61345","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-17","<p>The 2013 consultation on apprenticeship funding reforms sought evidence on the feasibility and impact of three different models for reforming apprenticeship funding. Following consideration of the responses to these, the second consultation sought views on two models—a PAYE model and an apprenticeship credit—that are consistent with an employer-driven apprenticeships system. A pure provider payment model was ruled out, as evidence from the first consultation indicated that this model was the least likely to deliver the intended aim of giving employers true purchasing power.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-06-17T09:54:31.0841182Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61345/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61345/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61345/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-11","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, for what reason the option of maintaining the current provider-funded model was dropped in his Department's second consultation on funding reform for apprenticeships.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","200174"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61346","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-16","<p>HMRC have taken part in discussions between Mapeley and Network Rail at the Priory Court Dover site on proposals for the construction of a multi storey car park on land adjacent to Priory Court not owned by either Mapeley or HMRC. Further discussions of future proposals have been between Mapeley as the freehold owner of Priory Court and Network Rail. HMRC have no outstanding enquiries from Mapeley.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-06-16T14:29:21.4122603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61346/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61346/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61346/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-11","Mapeley","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he expects HM Revenue and Customs to respond to Mapeley Estates, agents for the Custom House site, on the development of the new parking facilities at Dover Priory Railway Station.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","200178"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61347","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-16","<p>HMRC monitors the financial position of its key suppliers under agreed transparency arrangements. HMRC is unable to provide confidential financial information relating to its suppliers.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-06-16T14:51:14.4273074Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61347/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61347/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61347/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-11","Mapeley","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the profitability and financial position of Mapeley Steps Contractor Limited in its role of managing the HM Revenue and Customs' estate.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","200193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61348","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-16","<p>The Prudential Regulation Authority and the Financial Conduct Authority are responsible for overseeing the authorisation of insurance companies. The Treasury does not publish data on authorisations of insurance providers.</p><p> </p><p>This question has been passed on to the Financial Conduct Authority and the Prudential Regulation Authority, and they will reply directly to the honourable member by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-06-16T16:05:53.3142795Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61348/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61348/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61348/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-11","Insurance Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many businesses (a) applied for and (b) were granted authorisation as insurers in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Mark Hoban","Fareham","Mr Mark Hoban","200244"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61349","Department of Health","false","2014-06-16","<p>The requested information is not collected centrally. The Investment in General Practice report published by the Health and Social Care Information Centre includes the investment in General Practice and the reimbursement of drugs dispensed in General Practices at national level. A copy has been placed in the Library.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-06-16T16:23:46.6056633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61349/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61349/answer","PQ200278 - Lib Doc - Report.pdf","PQ200278 - Lib Doc - Report.pdf","Investment in General Practice","Investment in General Practice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61349/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","General Practitioners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to the Answer to the hon. Member for Suffolk Coastal of 8 January 2014, Official Report, column 265W, on general practitioners: Suffolk, how much his Department spent funding each general practice in England in 2012-13; and what spending type and GP Practice code applies in each case.","false","Biography information for Mr Mark Hoban","Fareham","Mr Mark Hoban","200278"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61350","Home Office","false","2014-06-18","<p>We will study the Court of Appeal judgment in MM and Others closely when this is handed down. We will then decide and announce how we will deal with those applications placed on hold pending the conclusion of the litigation.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-06-18T12:26:23.0252361Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61350/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61350/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61350/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61350/answer/previousversion/1319","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-11","Entry Clearances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the Answer of 17 March 2014, Official Report, column 364W, on entry clearances, what options the policy and operational teams in her Department are considering to best accommodate a clearance programme once the appeal against the judgment of Mr Justice Blake on 5 July 2013 on the Government's visa income threshold is published.","false","Biography information for Mr David Ward","Bradford East","Mr David Ward","200282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61351","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-17","<p><strong>The Government's Reasons for Specification Notice, published on 5 June 2014, explains in detail why the Government believes that the project is of a scale and complexity that would threaten Thames Water's ability to provide services to its customers. Paragraphs 21 to 35 provide this explanation.</strong></p><p> </p><p><strong>The Reasons Notice is available from the following link: </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/thames-tideway-tunnel-project-specification-and-preparatory-work-notices" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/thames-tideway-tunnel-project-specification-and-preparatory-work-notices</a></strong></p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-06-17T15:19:26.6548164Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61351/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61351/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61351/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-11","Thames Tideway Tunnel","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the ability of Thames Water to service the costs of building the proposed Thames Tideway Tunnel.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","200297"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61352","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-17","<p>Three guarantees and one Stand-by Facility have been signed under the UK Guarantees Scheme with a total value of £1,090,800,000. This includes Drax Power (£75m), Sustainable Development Capital – UK Energy Efficiency Investment Funds (£8.8m), Northern Line Extension (£750m) and Mersey Gateway Bridge (£257m).</p><p> </p><p>Any guarantees signed are reported to Parliament as required by the legislation, Infrastructure (Financial Assistance) Act 2012, underpinning the Scheme and can also be found on the gov.uk website.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-06-17T15:18:07.3930185Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61352/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61352/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61352/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-11","Infrastructure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, which infrastructure projects have accessed the UK Guarantees scheme; and how much funding was issued in each such case.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","200328"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61353","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-17","<p><strong>The Government has not proposed a guarantee for the Thames Tideway Tunnel. It has instead put in place a package of contingent financial support designed to cover low probability but high impact risks, prioritising the delivery of value for money for both taxpayers and customers. Further details are provided by the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs in a Written Ministerial Statement on 5 June. </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong>This statement is published in Hansard at: <a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmhansrd/cm140605/wmstext/140605m0001.htm#14060532000008" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmhansrd/cm140605/wmstext/140605m0001.htm#14060532000008</a></strong></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-06-17T15:20:50.8178979Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61353/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61353/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61353/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-11","Thames Tideway Tunnel","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what financial risk assessment he has carried out in respect of offering guarantees for the proposed Thames Tideway Tunnel.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","200335"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61354","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-18","<p> </p><p>The Ministry of Defence does not intend to provide any new buildings as part of the sale of the Defence Support Group. But as part of our planned drawdown from Germany there will be a requirement to provide Controlled Humidity Environment storage facilities as part of Army 2020.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-18T16:14:50.1930857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61354/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61354/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61354/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-11","Defence Support Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what new buildings his Department plans to provide for the use of the private sector partner taking over the Defence Support Group; and what the potential cost to the public purse is of such provision.","false","Biography information for Alison Seabeck","Plymouth, Moor View","Alison Seabeck","200326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61355","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-17","<p>The Office for Budget Responsibility (OBR) is responsible for producing independent economic and fiscal forecasts. The effects of payment protection insurance repayments were taken into account in their latest forecast of the economy, published in the March 2014 Economic and Fiscal Outlook.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-06-17T15:02:47.9028884Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61355/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61355/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61355/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-11","Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the contribution to economic growth of payment protection insurance repayments.","false","Biography information for Frank Dobson","Holborn and St Pancras","Frank Dobson","200336"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61356","Home Office","false","2014-07-01","<p> </p><p>Her Majesty's Passport Office has not closed its office in Newport. There is <br>an office in Newport providing counter fast track and premium services, <br>interviews for first time adult applicants and the Customer Contact Centre.<br><br>During 2011-12 as part of a wider operations restructuring, postal passport <br>application processing ceased in Newport and the office was relocated. It is <br>estimated that this reduced operational costs by around £2.6 million per year.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-01T13:37:03.7838566Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61356/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61356/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61356/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61356/answer/previousversion/1293","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-11","HM Passport Office: Newport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much her Department saved for the Exchequer by closing the Passport Office in Newport.","false","Biography information for Wayne David","Caerphilly","Wayne David","200286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61357","Home Office","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>Her Majesty's Passport Office have been training and redeploying staff from <br>other duties within the Agency, from other parts of the wider Home Office, and <br>in the case of one individual another Government department, to meet the <br>exceptional levels of passport demand. There will be some additional costs <br>relating to staff where they will be temporarily working away from their normal <br>workplace and where overtime is worked by staff from other parts of the <br>Department. At this time it is not possible to put a reliable estimate on <br>these additional costs.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-08T14:11:37.1164512Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61357/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61357/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61357/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61357/answer/previousversion/1295","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-11","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much the recently employed additional staff in passport offices are estimated to cost.","false","Biography information for Wayne David","Caerphilly","Wayne David","200287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61358","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-17","<p> </p><p>The recommended Body Mass Index (BMI) guidelines for entry into service in the Royal Navy are attached.</p><p> </p><p>Further assessment is by measurement of waist circumference: males with a BMI over 28 may join if their waist circumference is less than 94cm; females may join if their waist circumference is less than 80 cm.</p><p> </p><p>The standards do not change during the application process but BMI is measured as part of the medical assessment, and results may differ from a candidates' individual declaration and/or the outcome of the initial BMI check.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","200285","2014-06-17T16:04:26.1943676Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61358/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61358/answer","200285 Body Mass Index.doc","200285 Body Mass Index.doc","Body Mass Index","Body Mass Index","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61358/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-11","Navy: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the acceptable body mass index requirement is for an applicant to the Royal Navy.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","200275"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61359","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-17","<p> </p><p>The recommended Body Mass Index (BMI) guidelines for entry into service in the Royal Navy are attached.</p><p> </p><p>Further assessment is by measurement of waist circumference: males with a BMI over 28 may join if their waist circumference is less than 94cm; females may join if their waist circumference is less than 80 cm.</p><p> </p><p>The standards do not change during the application process but BMI is measured as part of the medical assessment, and results may differ from a candidates' individual declaration and/or the outcome of the initial BMI check.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","200275","2014-06-17T16:04:26.0849324Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61359/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61359/answer","200285 Body Mass Index.doc","200285 Body Mass Index.doc","Body Mass Index","Body Mass Index","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61359/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-11","Navy: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether applicants to the Royal Navy who meet an initial body mass index requirement of 28 face a different check at any other stage of the process.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","200285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61360","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-18","<p> </p><p>Information on students awarded and paid Disabled Students' Allowance is published annually by Student Loans Company (SLC) in the Statistical First Release ‘<em>Student Support for Higher Education England</em>'. The latest statistics are available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.slc.co.uk/media/694170/slcsfr052013.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.slc.co.uk/media/694170/slcsfr052013.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>A further breakdown for Birmingham Northfield constituency has been provided in the table for the academic year 2012/13. Equivalent figures for the academic year 2013/14 will be available from November 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Current DSA recipients and disabled students applying for DSAs in 2014/15 will not be affected by these changes in 2015/16.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We are currently consulting with a wide range of stakeholders and are working through the detail of how the changes will work in practice, including the number of students affected.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>Students in receipt of Disabled Students Allowance<sup>[1]</sup> from Birmingham, Northfield constituency</strong></p><p> </p><p>Academic Year 2012/13</p><p> </p><p>Effective date: 13/11/2013</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td colspan="4"><p>Application Type</p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p>Full-Time Application</p></td><td><p>Part-Time Application</p></td><td><p>Post Graduate DSA</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(Area)</p></td><td><p>No of Applicants Paid</p></td><td><p>No of Applicants Paid</p></td><td><p>No of Applicants Paid</p></td><td><p>No of Applicants Paid</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Birmingham Northfield Constituency<sup>[2]</sup></p></td><td><p>110</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>120</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p> </p><p>[1] Disabled Student Allowance may be paid to the Student or to a Supplier on the student's behalf.</p><p> </p><p>[2] Figures are derived from the Post Code of the applicant's home address.</p><p> </p><p>[3] The effective date is that of the November 2013 Awards Statistical First Release. The figures are therefore provisional and do not include students who were awarded DSA after November 2013.</p><p> </p><p>[4] DSA Payments may be made at any point during the Academic Year or after the end of the Academic Year.</p><p> </p><p>[5] Numbers are rounded to the nearest 10. Totals do not add to the sum of the components due to rounding.</p><p> </p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts",,"2014-06-18T15:38:40.4117907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61360/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61360/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61360/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-11","Disabled Students' Allowances: Birmingham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many people in Birmingham Northfield constituency qualify for the disabled students' allowance (DSA); and how many such people will be negatively affected by proposed changes to DSA.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","200253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61361","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-06-19","<p /> <p /> <p>NOMS takes the issue of assaults very seriously. It currently has systems in place to deal with perpetrators quickly and robustly, with serious incidents referred to the police for prosecution. It is working closely with the police and CPS to develop a new joint protocol to report crimes in prison - this includes pushing for prosecutions when prison staff are attacked.</p><p> </p><p>The number of prisoner on officer assaults in England and Wales prisons for each year over the last five years is presented in Table 3.8 of the assaults tables in each Safety in Custody statistics bulletin. The latest bulletin can be found at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/safety-in-custody-statistics" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/collections/safety-in-custody-statistics</a>. The Ministry of Justice is not responsible for prisons in other administrations of the United Kingdom.</p><p> </p><p>Figures for the number of working days lost due to sickness arising from assaults on officers are shown in the table 1 below. The data in this table is based on approved claims for sick leave excusal, whereby a period of absence that can be attributed to an assault at work does not count against the officer's allowance of sick pay. It is not specifically recorded that the assaults were initiated by prisoners. Table 1 shows that staff sickness fluctuates from year to year.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Table 1: Number of working days lost by officers granted sick leave excusal for reasons of assault, 2005/6 to 2013/14</strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Working days lost with sick leave excusal granted</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Percent of all Sick</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>9020</p></td><td><p>2.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>8270</p></td><td><p>1.9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>10280</p></td><td><p>2.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>10330</p></td><td><p>2.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009-10</p></td><td><p>3950</p></td><td><p>0.7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008-09</p></td><td><p>9250</p></td><td><p>1.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007-08</p></td><td><p>12360</p></td><td><p>2.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2006-07</p></td><td><p>7440</p></td><td><p>1.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2005-06</p></td><td><p>11890</p></td><td><p>2.0</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-06-19T15:33:02.8738639Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61361/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61361/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61361/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-11","Prisons: Crimes of Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many assaults on prison officers were committed by inmates in UK prisons in the last five years; and how many working days were lost as a result of such assaults.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","200252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61362","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>The Department of Transport completed a comprehensive review of datasets held in August 2013 and this was made available via <a href="http://www.data.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.data.gov.uk</a> on 2<sup>nd</sup> September 2013. This included details of 470 datasets including full metadata for all unpublished datasets.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-16T15:50:20.0003278Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61362/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61362/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61362/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-11","Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he expects his Department's review of unpublished datasets to be completed.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","200191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61363","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-16","<p>The average age of self-employed individuals in the UK is 46 years old. This median age is also 46 years old and these figures are consistent across the three years from 2009-10 to 2011-12.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>These estimates are based on the Survey of Personal Incomes (SPI) for the years concerned. The SPI for 2012-13 will be available later in the year.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-06-16T14:26:38.4924758Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61363/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61363/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61363/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-11","Self-employed","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the (a) mean and (b) median age was of people who were registered as self-employed in (i) 2010, (ii) 2011, (iii) 2012 and (iv) 2013.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","200314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61364","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-16","<p>Estimates of the numbers of individuals with self employment sources are published in HMRC's National Statistics table 3.10 which is available at the following internet address:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/income-of-individuals-with-self-employment-sources-2010-to-2011" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/income-of-individuals-with-self-employment-sources-2010-to-2011</a></p><p> </p><p>The numbers of individuals making zero profits and at other income levels is also shown in these tables.</p><p> </p><p>Tables for 2009-10 and earlier years are available from the National Archives internet site at the following address:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20121102223513/http:/hmrc.gov.uk/stats/income_distribution/menu-by-year.htm" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20121102223513/http:/hmrc.gov.uk/stats/income_distribution/menu-by-year.htm</a></p><p> </p><p>Overall, these show a long term trend of growth in the numbers of self-employed people.</p><p> </p><p>The Survey of Personal Incomes (SPI) for 2012-13 will be available later in the year.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-06-16T14:46:16.2849563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61364/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61364/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61364/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-11","Self-employed","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people were registered with HM Revenue and Customs as self-employed in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012 and (d) 2013; and how many of them reported net income (i) of zero and (ii) below the threshold for National Insurance in each year.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","200315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61365","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-16","<p>The number of New Enterprise Allowance starts since its commencement is regularly published by the Department and can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pre-work-programme-support-new-enterprise-allowance-march-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pre-work-programme-support-new-enterprise-allowance-march-2014</a></p><p> </p><p>The Department has made an assessment of number of New Enterprise Allowance participants returning to any out-of-work benefit, in the following published analysis. This suggests that 78% of people who started drawing the New Enterprise Allowance remained off benefit continuously for 12 months.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/225167/NEA_benefit_status_ad-hoc_v3.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/225167/NEA_benefit_status_ad-hoc_v3.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>With regards to the number registered with HM Revenue and Customs; the Department does not hold individual level data on self-employment with which we would be able to make this assessment.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-06-16T15:32:35.2588599Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61365/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61365/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61365/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-11","New Enterprise Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people have received the New Enterprise Allowance since its commencement; and how many such people have subsequently (a) returned to jobseeker's allowance and (b) registered with HM Revenue and Customs as self-employed.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","200334"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61366","Department of Health","false","2014-06-16","<p>NHS England has a number of interim policies in place, including the policy for the provision of in vitro fertilisation (IVF) for Armed Forces personnel.</p><p> </p><p>A review of the interim policy in relation to the provision of IVF for Armed Forces personnel has recently been undertaken. Following detailed costing of a move to the levels recommended in the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence guideline, it was agreed in May 2014 to increase the number of cycles of IVF to three if clinically appropriate and if eligibility criteria are met.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-06-16T16:13:06.4068202Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61366/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61366/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61366/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","Armed Forces: In Vitro Fertilisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, for what reasons the policy of NHS England on the number of cycles of IVF it provides to armed forces personnel is to provide fewer than the number recommended by National Institute for Health and Care Excellence.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","200338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61367","Department of Health","false","2014-06-16","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) has not yet published its final quality standard on fertility. NICE's Clinical Commissioning Group Outcomes Indicator Set (CCGOIS) Advisory Committee makes recommendations on potential indicators derived from its published guidance and quality standards for inclusion in the CCGOIS which are then considered by NHS England.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-06-16T15:24:53.7679354Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61367/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61367/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61367/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","Fertility","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether the forthcoming National Institute for Health and Care Excellence quality standard on fertility will be considered for a CCG Outcome Indicator.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","200339"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61368","Department of Health","false","2014-06-16","<p>There are strict legal controls governing the sale and supply of medicinal products in the United Kingdom.</p><p> </p><p>The Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency (MHRA) considers Melanotan products to be medicinal products within the meaning of the Human Medicines Regulations 2012 and as such, the manufacture, sale and supply are subject to UK regulatory control. No Melanotan product holds a marketing authorisation (product licence) for use in the UK and consequently advertising and sale or supply would be in breach of regulatory requirements.</p><p> </p><p>The MHRA is aware that Melanotan is being sold through some outlets such as gyms and beauty salons and is available more widely on the Internet through certain websites.</p><p> </p><p>During the past 12 months, the MHRA has worked with Internet Service Providers in the UK and abroad to suspend more than 100 websites illegally trading in Melanotan.</p><p> </p><p>The MHRA issues regular warnings to the public about the dangers involved in the use of unlicensed medicines, including Melanotan and officials have participated in Press campaigns and specific media coverage of the problem.</p><p> </p><p>As of 12 June 2014, the MHRA has received a total of 22 reports of Adverse Drug Reactions associated with the use of Melanotan (product names Melanotan I, Melanotan II and Ubertan), describing a total of 93 adverse reactions. However, it is important to note that the reporting of a suspected adverse reaction does not necessarily mean it is related to the drug.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-06-16T13:47:09.317935Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61368/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61368/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61368/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","Melanotan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the (a) prevalence and (b) effect of the sale of the unlicensed drug Melanotan (i) online and (ii) in shops.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","200340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61369","Department of Health","false","2014-06-16","<p>675 partners are currently signed up the Responsibility Deal. Details of these partners, the pledges they are committed to taking action on and their annual updates are available in full on the Responsibility Deal website at:</p><p> </p><p>https://responsibilitydeal.dh.gov.uk/partners/</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-06-16T14:20:28.3025226Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61369/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61369/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61369/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","Health: Business","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate his Department has made of the number of companies who have signed up to one or more pledges set out in the Responsibility Deal; and what estimate he has made of the proportion of those companies which are meeting all of the pledges they have signed up to.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","200341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61370","Department of Health","false","2014-06-16","<p>My Rt. Hon. Friend, the Secretary of State for Health, has had a number of discussions with senior members of NHS England's executive team on the performance of the National Health Service against the waiting time targets for cancer treatment, but not with the National Clinical Director for Cancer.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-06-16T15:19:32.7136766Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61370/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61370/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61370/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with the National Clinical Director for Cancer on the performance of the NHS against the waiting time targets for cancer treatment.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","200342"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61371","Department for Education","false","2014-06-16","<p>My noble Friend, the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Schools, responded to the hon. Member's other letter of 30 April about admission arrangements at Walsall academy on 16 June. On behalf of the Department I would like to apologise for the delay in answering this letter.</p><p> </p><p>My reply of 10 June related to the letter with the reference (2014/0036207) quoted in the question.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-06-16T14:02:24.8319089Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61371/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61371/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61371/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-11","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 10 June 2014 Official Report, column 74W, on Members: Correspondence, when he expects to send a substantive reply to the letter of 30 April 2014 from the hon. Member for Walsall North about admissions to Walsall Academy which was separate from the letter sent to the Chief Executive of the Education Funding Agency; and for what reason that Answer does not mention that there was separate correspondence on the subject.","false","Biography information for Mr David Winnick","Walsall North","Mr David Winnick","200309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61373","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-07-14","<p>Arts Council England (ACE) makes its funding decisions independently of Government and as such we do not hold the information requested. However, the following information has been provided by ACE:</p><p> </p><p>Value of ACE awards to applicants resident in ASHFIELD Constituency 2009 2014</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Decision Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Value of Awards</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Per-Capita*</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>£9,706</p></td><td><p>£0.10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>£9,712</p></td><td><p>£0.10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>£13,500</p></td><td><p>£0.13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>* based on Mid-2011 population estimate (ONS) 101,914.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, ACE made two other awards totalling £3.8m from which Ashfield can benefit</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-07-14T11:04:56.789158Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61373/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61373/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61373/answer","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61373/answer/previousversion/1530","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-06-11","Arts: Ashfield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much the Arts Council has spent per head of population in Ashfield constituency in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","200247"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61374","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>At the Autumn Statement we announced a £1 billion package of business rates support to help shops and local firms. This included a £1,000 discount for two years for smaller shops, pubs and restaurants. We do not hold figures for numbers benefitting from that measure in the Ashfield constituency. However, based on local authority reports of the amount of relief awarded, we estimate that 420 properties will benefit within the boundary of Ashfield District Council, 400 in <a href="http://www.bassetlaw.gov.uk/" target="_blank">Bassetlaw District Council</a>, 250 in <a title="Link to Broxtowe Borough Council's website" href="http://www.broxtowe.gov.uk/" target="_blank">Broxtowe Borough Council</a>, 370 in <a href="http://www.gedling.gov.uk/" target="_blank">Gedling Borough Council</a>, 460 in <a href="http://www.mansfield.gov.uk/" target="_blank">Mansfield District Council</a>, 500 in <a href="http://www.newark-sherwooddc.gov.uk/" target="_blank">Newark and Sherwood District Council</a>, 320 in <a href="http://www.rushcliffe.gov.uk/" target="_blank">Rushcliffe Borough Council</a>, and 1,000 in Nottingham Unitary Authority.</p><p>The support package also included a 50 per cent discount for businesses taking on long-term empty shops, the doubling of small business rate relief for another year, a 2% cap on RPI increases for 2014/2015, and allowing businesses to spread their rates payments over 12 months.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-06-16T15:29:46.6530658Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61374/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61374/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61374/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-06-11","Non-domestic Rates: Nottinghamshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many businesses in (a) Ashfield constituency and (b) Nottinghamshire have qualified for the full £1,000 business rates discount to date.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","200189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61375","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-16","<p>Statistics on the number of additional rate income tax payers liable to pay the by government office regions, including the East Midlands, are published in HMRC's income tax statistics, table 2.2: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/306856/Table_2.2.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/306856/Table_2.2.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>County and constituency level information on additional rate tax payers is not published.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-06-16T14:28:09.8542197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61375/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61375/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61375/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-11","Income Tax: Nottinghamshire","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people in (a) Ashfield constituency and (b) Nottinghamshire paid the top rate of income tax in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","200187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61376","Cabinet Office","false","2014-06-16","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-06-16T10:00:53.31",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61376/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61376/answer","PQ 200186.pdf","PQ 200186.pdf","ONS Letter to Member","ONS Letter to Member","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61376/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-06-11","Average Earnings: Ashfield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the average salary was for a (a) man and (b) woman of (i) white ethnic origin and (ii) black and minority ethnic origin and who was (A) disabled and (B) not disabled in Ashfield constituency in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","200186"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61377","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>a-i) Over the 5 year period 1st April 2009 to 31st March 2014 on average each sector skills council received £11m of public funding from the UK Commission for Employment as follows:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="5"><p>Average funding per SSC</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>09/10</p></td><td><p>10-11</p></td><td><p>11-12</p></td><td><p>12-13</p></td><td><p>13-14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>National</p></td><td><p>2.9m</p></td><td><p>2.3m</p></td><td><p>2.3m</p></td><td><p>2.1m</p></td><td><p>1.8m</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>a-ii) Public funding from the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills is allocated to sector skills councils by the UK Commission for Employment and Skills at a national level for sector skills councils to decide how to best use the resources available to them including any specific support at a local level.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>b) The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills does not hold information on the amount of private funding provided to each sector skills council.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-06-16T16:13:30.068955Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61377/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61377/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61377/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-11","Sector Skills Councils","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how much (a) public and (b) private funding has been provided to each sector skills council (i) on average and (ii) in the East Midlands in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","200188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61378","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p>A number of factors contributed to the problems experienced with the Information Communication Technology hosting environment provided for Capita. I refer the hon. Member to the Secretary of State for Defence's (Philip Hammond) response to an Urgent Question from the hon. Member for Gedling (Vernon Coaker) on 14 January 2014 (Official Report, column 715).</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-06-24T14:59:39.8039332Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61378/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61378/answer","Hansard Extract 200298.doc","Hansard Extract 200298.doc","Hansard Extract 14 January 2014","Hansard Extract 14 January 2014","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61378/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61378/answer/previousversion/3504","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-11","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reason his Department did not provide an ICT hosting environment for Capita on time for the Recruiting Partnering Project.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61379","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-17","<p> </p><p>The information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-17T16:00:19.0718859Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61379/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61379/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61379/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-11","ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what information and communications technology projects his Department has implemented (a) to the original deadline and on budget and (b) after the original deadline and over budget in the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61380","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p>No personnel have been reprimanded in connection with the delivery of the Recruiting Partnering Project.<br><br>An ICT hosting platform is being provided for Capita.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-06-24T14:31:40.3289762Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61380/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61380/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61380/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61380/answer/previousversion/3505","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-11","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what military or civilian personnel in his Department of what rank or grade have been reprimanded for failing to deliver an ICT hosting environment for Capita as part of the Recruiting Partnering Project.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61381","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-23","<p>Each branch of the Armed Forces has a distinctive brand that needs to be marketed separately in order to attract the best candidates. <br><br>Capturing the cost of recruiting across the Armed Forces is a complex and resource-intensive task. For financial year (FY) 2010-11, when both the recruitment budget and recruitment targets were below normal levels, these calculations were not carried out. The costs of recruiting programmes for FYs 2009-10, 2011-12 and 2012-13 are set out in the following table. The cost of recruiting in FY 2013-14 will be available in early 2015.<br><br></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Financial Year</strong></td><td><strong>Royal Navy (£)</strong></td><td><strong>Army (£)</strong></td><td><strong>RAF (£)</strong></td><td><strong>Total (£)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>2009-10</td><td>41,475,281</td><td>138,743,300</td><td>51,298,179</td><td>231,516,760</td></tr><tr><td>2011-12</td><td>32,017,364</td><td>134,595,989</td><td>38,702,993</td><td>205,316,346</td></tr><tr><td>2012-13</td><td>33,228,059</td><td>122,756,649</td><td>35,430,723</td><td>191,415,431</td></tr></tbody></table><p>As reductions have been made to force levels recruitment levels have been adjusted but not stopped as the Services are required to keep recruiting to maintain the right skills.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-06-23T15:43:48.9854719Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61381/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61381/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61381/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61381/answer/previousversion/3509","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-11","Armed Forces: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will estimate (a) the savings generated by each branch of the armed forces having separate recruiting programmes and (b) the annual cost of each such programme.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61382","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p>The cost of the Recruiting &amp; Partnering Project to date (for the three years from March 2011-2014) is around £300 million. This figure includes the costs of the service provider, CAPITA and costs to the Ministry of Defence such as military and civilian manpower, Information Communication Technology provision and infrastructure.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-06-24T14:32:34.4859596Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61382/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61382/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61382/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61382/answer/previousversion/3507","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-11","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost to the public purse to date is of the Recruiting and Partnering Project.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200320"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61383","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p>My right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Defence (Philip Hammond) set out on 14 January 2014 (Official Report, column 716) the cost of Capita providing a new Information Technology platform as part of the Recruiting Partnering Project. At the time, these costs were expected to be around £47.7 million directly linked to the change of hosting provision. Since this statement, the £47.7 million has reduced to £42.9 million. <br><br>As previously stated by the Secretary of State on 14 January, there has been an additional cost of around £1 million per month to run the Capita system. This includes costs for additional manpower. <br><br>The Recruiting Partnering Project remains within the overall agreed cost of £1.360 billion.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","200538","2014-06-24T14:51:44.6111409Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61383/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61383/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61383/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61383/answer/previousversion/3506","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-11","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reason the initial estimate of the additional costs of reverting to the fallback position of a hosting solution provided by Capita for the Recruiting Partnering Project increased from £47.7 million to £70 million; and who was responsible for these estimates.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61384","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-18","<p> </p><p>I have not made such an assessment. The UK Government's Scotland Analysis Programme identified benefits for UK businesses from common rules and institutions that create a larger domestic market, reduce administrative burdens and encourage fair competition. Diverging regulatory regimes and new burdens created by an international border may affect the level of trade (£48 billion from Scotland to rest of UK in 2012, and £59 billion in the opposite direction) and the 30,000 people who currently travel freely between Scotland and North England each day to work.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-18T15:39:58.9953749Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61384/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61384/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61384/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-11","Business","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the potential effects of Scottish independence on businesses in the North East and Cumbria.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","200254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61385","Cabinet Office","false","2014-06-16","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-06-16T10:02:10.203",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61385/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61385/answer","PQ 200227.pdf","PQ 200227.pdf","ONS Letter to Member","ONS Letter to Member","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61385/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-06-11","Average Earnings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what adjusted change there has been in average gross weekly earnings of (a) full-time workers, (b) men working full-time and (c) women working full-time since January 2010.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","200227"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61386","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-18","<p> </p><p>We are currently consulting with a wide range of stakeholders to help inform both the Equality Analysis and Disabled Students' Allowances Guidance for 2015/16.</p><p> </p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts",,"2014-06-18T15:41:43.2719943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61386/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61386/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61386/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-11","Disabled Students' Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to his Written Statement of 7 April 2014, Official Report, column 1WS on higher education, what public consultation he has undertaken on the proposed changes to disabled students' allowance.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","200271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61387","Department of Health","false","2014-06-16","<p>No assessment has been made centrally. NHS England is responsible for the commissioning of primary care health services and for securing the best possible outcomes for patients.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-06-16T13:24:54.9490619Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61387/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61387/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61387/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","Health Services: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the quality of provision of primary care in Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","200222"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61388","Department of Health","false","2014-06-16","<p>These are matters for the local National Health Service. The hon. Member should engage with the NHS at a local level.</p><p> </p><p>This Government is committed to devolving decision-making about local NHS services to local clinicians and communities. It is general practitioners clinicians, patients and local authorities who are best placed to determine the nature of their NHS services.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-06-16T13:50:31.3989068Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61388/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61388/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-11","Health Services: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will meet the hon. Member for Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland to discuss the proposed closure of (a) minor injuries units at Guisborough and East Cleveland Hospitals, (b) Skelton Medical Centre, (c) Park End Clinic and (d) Skelton NHS Walk-in-Centre.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","200221"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61389","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>Local Enterprise Partnerships (LEP) board membership is a matter for LEPs themselves and they are best placed to ensure it meets the needs of their businesses and local people.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-16T16:02:14.4904594Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61389/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61389/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61389/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-11","Local Enterprise Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the extent to which there is a gender imbalance in the composition of Local Enterprise Partnership boards.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","200232"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61390","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-17","<p>Beyond the powers in the Scotland Act 2012, the Government has no plans for further devolution of tax powers to Scotland until the referendum on Scottish independence has been settled</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Budget 2014 announced the reform of air passenger duty with the abolition of bands C and D from 1 April 2015. This will eliminate the two highest rates of air passenger duty charged on flights to countries over 4,000 miles from Britain, cutting tax for millions for passengers to travelling to China, India, Brazil and many other emerging markets. This will mean that flights to South Asia and the Caribbean will pay tax at the lower band B rate.</p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan",,"2014-06-17T14:39:47.3161602Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61390/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61390/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-11","Air Passenger Duty: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to devolve Air Passenger Duty to Scotland.","false","Biography information for Angus Brendan MacNeil","Na h-Eileanan an Iar","Mr Angus Brendan MacNeil","200267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61391","Home Office","false","2014-10-07","<p>The information is not available in the format requested. Information can be <br>provided for UK straightforward and non-straightforward applications as set out <br>below for 2013-14<br><br>Total number of UK applications received 2013-14 5,818,272<br><br>Processed outside published turnaround times<br>Straightforward (within 3 <br>weeks) <br>401 (0.007% of applications received)<br><br>Non-straightforward (within 6 weeks) <br>29,331 (0.5% of applications received)</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-10-07T15:55:35.6808333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61391/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61391/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-11","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people have waited longer than the advised waiting times for (a) new passport applications and (b) passport renewals in the last year.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","200255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61392","Home Office","false","2014-07-07","<p> </p><p>Ministers receive regular reports on the performance of Her Majesty's Passport Office.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-07T15:34:47.5450088Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61392/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61392/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-11","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent reports she has received of changes in the backlog for processing (a) new passport applications and (b) passport renewals.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","200256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61393","Home Office","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>The Home Office Counting Rules provide guidance to police forces on all matters that relate to the recording of crime and disposals. They are issued annually <br>by the Home Office. <br><br>This Government is committed to increasing the transparency of information available to the public on recorded crime and outcomes. From April 2014, we introduced the recorded crime outcomes framework, replacing the previous regime of detections. This will inform the public how forces have dealt with 100% of crimes reported to them. For the first time, therefore, the public will be able to see how those crimes previously recorded as ‘undetected' and as requiring ‘no further action' have been resolved. The first data will be available in July 2015.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-06-16T15:52:38.0103762Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61393/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61393/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-11","Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what guidance her Department issues to police forces on marking cases as requiring No Further Action.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","200257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61394","Home Office","false","2014-10-01","<p> </p><p>We are unable to break the data down into first time applications and renewals, <br>although we can provide the data broken down by straightforward and <br>non-straightforward.<br><br>The table below shows the average waiting time for straightforward and <br>non-straightforward applications on an annual basis since 2010.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Average processing times in working days</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>Straightforward applications </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Non-straightforward applications</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>3.6</p></td><td><p>9.7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>4.1</p></td><td><p>9.7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>6.8</p></td><td><p>11.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>3.8</p></td><td><p>7.9</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-10-01T14:20:47.1714594Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61394/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61394/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61394/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-11","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the average waiting time for (a) new passport applications and (b) passport renewals in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","200258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61395","Home Office","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>The information requested is not held centrally by the Home Office. Until recently, information has only been collected on crime outcomes that involve action being taken by the police. These were part of the former detections framework before 2013/14, and the new outcomes framework after that.<br><br>In April 2014, a new, broader crime outcomes framework was introduced, providing much greater transparency on how crimes are resolved by the police. This framework includes all scenarios where no further action was taken by the police. From April 2014 onwards, data is being collected on this new framework, and the first full set of statistics will be published in July 2015.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-06-16T15:59:11.4112294Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61395/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61395/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61395/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-11","Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the number and proportion of cases that police have marked as requiring No Further Action in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","200259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61396","Home Office","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>The table below shows the number of complaints related to delays in receiving a <br>passport.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>Number of complaints relating to delays</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p>1253</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p>1341</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p>1513</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p>1437</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-08T14:14:16.4346113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61396/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61396/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61396/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-11","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many complaints her Department has received regarding delays to the issuing of a passport in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","200216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61397","Home Office","true","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p>During the period between 1 June 2013 and 31 May 2014, Her Majesty's Passport Office <br />received <del class="ministerial">1,446,983</del> <ins class="ministerial">1,425,885</ins> first time passport applications and <del class="ministerial">4,528,751</del> <ins class="ministerial">4,461,343</ins> passport <br />renewal applications.<br /><br />This compares with 1,346,246 first time applications and 4,036,267 passport <br />renewal applications during the period between 1 June 2012 and 31 May 2013.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-08T14:03:02.687Z","2014-09-02T14:35:59.8202456Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61397/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61397/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61397/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61397/answer/previousversion/8681","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-11","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many applications for (a) new passports and (b) passport renewals there have been in the last year; and what the annual change in such figures has been.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","200217"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61398","Home Office","false","2014-06-18","<p>We expect the new statutory licensing regime for those conducting the activity of private investigations to come into force in 2015.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-06-18T12:24:43.7911707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61398/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61398/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-11","Private Investigators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the Answer of 13 May 2014, Official Report, column 462W, on private investigation, on what date she expects the new statutory licensing requirement to come into force.","false","Biography information for Lord Garnier","Harborough","Sir Edward Garnier","200171"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61399","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-18","<p> </p><p>The cost of providing an Apprenticeship is highly variable.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In 2012, the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) commissioned a report from The Institute for Employment Research entitled: “Employer Investment in Apprenticeships and Workplace Learning”</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/32306/12-814-employer-investment-in-apprenticeships-fifth-net-benefits-study.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/32306/12-814-employer-investment-in-apprenticeships-fifth-net-benefits-study.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The report gives details of the costs of Apprenticeships to employers in several sectors for 16-18 year olds and for 19-24 year olds. It also compares the contribution of employers to that of the state.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","200240 ; 200293","2014-06-18T15:56:10.9522291Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61399/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61399/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61399/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-11","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the average annual cost of training an apprentice aged 16 to 18 is; and what proportion of such costs is borne by (a) the public purse, (b) individuals and (c) employers.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Mr Liam Byrne","200239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61400","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-18","<p> </p><p>The cost of providing an Apprenticeship is highly variable.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In 2012, the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) commissioned a report from The Institute for Employment Research entitled: “Employer Investment in Apprenticeships and Workplace Learning”</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/32306/12-814-employer-investment-in-apprenticeships-fifth-net-benefits-study.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/32306/12-814-employer-investment-in-apprenticeships-fifth-net-benefits-study.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The report gives details of the costs of Apprenticeships to employers in several sectors for 16-18 year olds and for 19-24 year olds. It also compares the contribution of employers to that of the state.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","200239 ; 200293","2014-06-18T15:56:11.0772368Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61400/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61400/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61400/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-11","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the average unit cost per year to train an apprentice aged 19 to 24 is; and what proportion of such costs is borne by (a) the public purse, (b) apprentices and (c) employers.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Mr Liam Byrne","200240"
